Executive Profile
Mark A. Pytosh  Chief Executive Officer of CVR GP LLC, President of CVR GP LLC and Director of CVR GP LLC, CVR Partners, LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships52$2,381,189As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Mark A. Pytosh has been Chief Executive Officer and President at Rentech Nitrogen Partners, L.P. since April 1, 2016. Mr. Pytosh has been the Chief Executive Officer of CVR GP, LLC since May 5, 2014 and serves its President since May 2014. Mr. Pytosh served as the Chief Financial Officer of Tervita Corporation (formerly CCS Corporation) from 2011 to January 20, 2014 and served as its Executive Vice President. Mr. Pytosh joined Tervita Corporation in April 2010. He ... served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at Covanta Holding Corporation of Covanta Energy Corporation from September 1, 2006 to March 2010 and served as its Senior Vice President from September 1, 2006 to December 2007. Before joining Lehman Brothers in 2000, he had 15 years of investment banking experience at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette and Kidder, Peabody. Mr. Pytosh was the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Waste Services Inc. from February 23, 2004 to August 31, 2006, where he had many management responsibilities for corporate development, corporate finance, treasury and investor relations. Prior to 2004, he spent 18 years in investment banking, working with a broad range of clients in the environmental services, automotive, construction equipment and a variety of other industrial sectors. From 2000 to 2004, Mr. Pytosh was a Managing Director of Investment Banking at Lehman Brothers, where he led the Global Industrial Group. Mr. Pytosh has primary management responsibility for Corporate Development, Corporate Finance, Treasury and Investor Relations. He also focused on working with clients in the industrial sector including leading its banking efforts in the solid waste industry. Mr. Pytosh served as a Managing Director at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette, where he led the Environmental Services and Automotive Industry groups. He started his career at Kidder, Peabody. Mr. Pytosh began his 25-year career working for large investment banking institutions. Mr. Pytosh has industry-related experience and extensive financial background both in corporate and investment environments. Mr. Pytosh has been a Director of CVR GP, LLC, the General Partner of CVR Partners, LP. since June 2011. He has been a Director of Rentech Nitrogen Partners, L.P. since April 1, 2016. He serves as a Director at the University of Illinois Foundation. He serves as a Member of Executive Council of Cohesive Capital Partners. Mr. Pytosh received a B.S. in Chemistry from the University of Illinois in Urbana-Champaign.Read Full Background




